{{Blurimage|caption=An attempt to render all of Level 164 as a single object.|file=Pineapple1.jpg|hovertext=Mmm, pined apples}}

Level 164, otherwise known as 'Structures in the Soil', is a giant pineapple. The level has been thought to be directly connected to [[The Void|The Soil]], with few disputing that Level 164 should be an object instead of a standard level. Notably, the pineapple seems to never rot, staying fresh throughout day and night. This is most likely because of their connection to the soil.

The structures within Level 164 have little variety, with the most common being 'eyes' with spiky, shark complexion. These spikes are arranged in order of the Fibonacci Sequence, of which the reason is unknown. The skin of the pineapple is yellow, dry, and slightly cracked, seeming to cover the vast majority of the level, excluding structures.

The lighting in Level 164 is purely by the aforementioned 'eyes', which produce an ominous but sufficient glow for sight, which also enables the pineapple to undergo photosynthesis. The average temperature in the level ranges around 70-90 degrees Fahrenheit, although it has a complete lack of any wind, wanderers have noted a warm breeze washing over them at random times while exploring the level. This level is thought to be connected to [[The Frontrooms|the Frontrooms]], this is because it is simply a giant variation of ''Ananas comosus'', commonly known as a pineapple. Some people have falsely claimed that Level 164 is [[Level 164|a large, dark-skied complex akin to a suburban neighborhood, complete with several structures and its own distinguished phenomenons]]. However, this has been proven false, and such claims should be disregarded.

Other, less important details of the level, are details of '''Level 164''' that bare either none or negligible importance to any sort of survival in the level.   

Such details are the following;   
*The skin of the pineapple is sufficiently solid
*The Level is surrounded by a dark skybox on almost all sides and [[The Void|The Soil]] on the ground.
*Some patches of the level have piles of mulch on the ground.
*Eyes can be seen going straight up into the sky.

===The Leaf===
{{Blurimage|caption=A picture of the Leaf.|file=OIP (6).webp|hovertext=A constant green presence.}}
A structure in '''Level 164''', aptly named "The Leaf" is a structure that is partially separated from the rest of the level. The Leaf appears as a large leaf, in keeping with the leaves of the fruit of 'Ananas comosus'. The Leaf can be seen in most parts of '''Level 164''', as it floats above the level at around 2,500 feet from the surface<ref>It is notable to mention that the Leaf has an estimated length of 12,516 miles long.</ref>. It has been described to move around the level with a slithering-like motion.  

On extremely rare occasions, The Leaf can lower down to the level, making the columns touch the surface of '''Level 164'''. A disembodied roaring sound effect can be heard from parts of The Leaf. It is theoretically possible to get to the top of The Leaf, as rare few buildings are tall enough for climbing, but The Leaf has not encountered any of these buildings in any recorded times.  

===False Suns===

False suns are a phenomenon exclusive to '''Level 164'''. Not much is known about this phenomenon due to its enigmatic nature. False lights usually appear as miniature suns providing energy to the level. After a while, they would slowly dissipate into the darkness. It is also notable that these false lights do not produce any light to their surroundings.

False Suns have been appearing in '''Level 164''' at an increasing rate over the past twenty years, it is believed that it is in response to human activity.

==Entities==
Entities are relatively common within '''Level 164''', but not enough to pose any great danger to people inside the level. These entities usually include [[Entity 3|Grass Cells]], [[Entity 8|Pines]], and [[Entity 6|Planters]]. A select few reports have stated that [[Entity 24|Refuse]] have also lurked inside the level, but these reports have yet to be confirmed.

==Bases, Communities, and Outposts==
Due to an extreme lack of supplies, and any desire to, bases, communities, and outposts are absent in '''Level 164'''.

==Entrances and Exits== 

===Entrances===

* Planting tropical plants in [[Level 105]] may lead one to this level.
* Entering a nuclear cooling tower painted entirely in yellow with green smog in [[Level 174]] will lead to this level.

===Exits===

* Extremely rare cases of no-clipping into the grass will lead to [[Level 176]].
* It is thought that going high enough into the sky will potentially lead to most likely, [[The Void]].
* Sunbathing under False Suns may lead one to [[Level 87]].
* Noclipping through the piles of mulch sends one to [[Level 186]].
* Jumping off the Pineapple somehow is presumed to lead to [[The Void|The Soil]], but as there are no records of an edge this may be false.

